# Implementation Plan: API Rate Limiting & Bot Detection

We will add API rate limiting to protect the backend services from brute-force authentication attempts and spamming, and implement an **Admin Bot Detection & Rate Limit Monitor** to audit and analyze rate-limiting violations using Gemini AI.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> - Based on feedback, we **will not** configure `app.set('trust proxy', 1)` since the server is not behind a proxy.
> - We will install `express-rate-limit` at the root.
> - Rate limit violations will be logged directly to MongoDB in a new `RateLimitViolation` collection.
> - Admins will be able to request Gemini AI evaluation of rate limit offenders (analyzing their IP, endpoint frequency, account creation time, and violation patterns) to determine if the actor is a bot or an authentic person.

