### Backend Components

#### [NEW] [RateLimitViolation.js](file:///c:/Users/MOON/Desktop/nextProjects/socialAppZ/backend/models/RateLimitViolation.js)
- Define a schema to log violations:
  - `user`: ObjectId (optional, ref User)
  - `ip`: String
  - `endpoint`: String
  - `attemptedUsername`: String (helpful for login brute-force attempts)
  - `createdAt`: Date

#### [NEW] [rateLimiter.js](file:///c:/Users/MOON/Desktop/nextProjects/socialAppZ/backend/middlewares/rateLimiter.js)
- Implement rate limiting configurations:
  - **General API Limiter**: 100 requests per 15 minutes.
  - **Authentication Limiter**: 10 requests per 15 minutes.
  - **Spam Protection Limiter**: 20 post/comment creations per 15 minutes.
  - **Reports Limiter**: 10 reports per 15 minutes.
- Define a custom `handler` in the limiters that writes an entry to the `RateLimitViolation` collection before returning the standard 429 response.

#### [MODIFY] [admin.routes.js](file:///c:/Users/MOON/Desktop/nextProjects/socialAppZ/backend/routes/admin.routes.js)
- Add administrative routes:
  - `GET /rate-limit-violations`: Fetches recent rate limit violation incidents.
  - `POST /rate-limit-violations/:id/ai-analyze`: Evaluates an incident or user using Gemini AI to check if they behave like a automated bot or an authentic person.
  - `DELETE /rate-limit-violations/:id`: Dismisses/removes a rate limit alert.

#### [MODIFY] [admin.controller.js](file:///c:/Users/MOON/Desktop/nextProjects/socialAppZ/backend/controllers/admin.controller.js)
- Implement `getRateLimitViolations`, `deleteRateLimitViolation`, and `analyzeRateLimitViolationAI` controllers:
  - `analyzeRateLimitViolationAI` will query history for the offender's IP/userId, fetch their registration date (if user exists), and prompt Gemini AI to generate a bot-likelihood assessment (Verdict: Safe, Suspicious, or Bot, with reasoning).

#### [MODIFY] [server.js](file:///c:/Users/MOON/Desktop/nextProjects/socialAppZ/backend/server.js)
- Apply rate limiters:
  - Apply `generalLimiter` on `/api/`.
  - Apply `authLimiter` on `/api/auth/login` and `/api/auth/signup`.
  - Apply `spamLimiter` on `/api/posts` (POST post and POST comment routes).

